4.	What is the type of the DM backup file?

In interview contexts, the question "What is the type of the DM backup file?" is usually about SAP Data Migration (DM) or Database Management (DM) backups.
If it‚Äôs SAP Data Migration, the backup file type is typically .tar or .zip (compressed archive) depending on the export tool.
If it‚Äôs SAP Data Management / Data Services, backups are often in .atl (for repository exports) or .bak (for database backups).
If it‚Äôs Database Management, the answer depends on the DBMS:
SQL Server ‚Üí .bak
Oracle ‚Üí .dmp (Data Pump export)
PostgreSQL ‚Üí .backup
MySQL ‚Üí .sql

